Implementation details: We'll allocate a 32-bit bitmask maybe, but simple bool array of 26 is fine. Since we only care about letters a-z. For other characters, we could use a set via a map, but not needed.

Simplify: Use a []bool[26] allocated on stack? In Zig, we can use var seen = try allocator.allocator()._allocate(u8, 26)? But we can also use a fixed-size array of u8 bits. Simpler: use a 32-bit usize bitmask for 26 letters. We'll map letter index 0-25. For each char c (lowercase), set bit. If bit already set -> duplicate -> return false.

